SIMPLE: prefer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prefer
<hw>Pre*fer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Preferred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Preferring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧f⟦eacute⟧rer</ets>, L. <ets>praeferre</ets>;
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>ferre</ets> to bear or carry. See 1st
<er>Bear</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To carry or bring (something)
forward, or before one; hence, to bring for consideration, acceptance,
judgment, etc.; to offer; to present; to proffer; to address; -- said
especially of a request, prayer, petition, claim, charge, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He spake, and to her hand <qex>preferred</qex> the bowl.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Presently <qex>prefer</qex> his suit to C⟦ae⟧sar.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Three tongues <qex>prefer</qex> strange orisons on high.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go before, or be before, in estimation; to
outrank; to surpass.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Though maidenhood
<xex>prefer</xex> bigamy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cause to go before; hence, to advance before
others, as to an office or dignity; to raise; to exalt; to promote;
<as>as, to <ex>prefer</ex> an officer to the rank of
general</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would <qex>prefer</qex> him to a better place.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To set above or before something else in estimation,
favor, or liking; to regard or honor before another; to hold in greater
favor; to choose rather; -- often followed by <xex>to</xex>,
<xex>before</xex>, or <xex>above</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If I <qex>prefer</qex> not Jerusalem above my chief joy.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cxxxvii. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Preferred</qex> an infamous peace before a most just war.</q>
<rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Preferred stock</b></col>, <cd>stock which takes a
dividend before other capital stock; -- called also <altname>preference
stock</altname> and <altname>preferential stock</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To choose; elect. See <er>Choose</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preferability</ent>⟦br⟧
